{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "To extract comprehensive audio features, we chose the COVAREP toolkit [14].",
    "COVAREP is an open-source audio analysis toolkit capable of extracting a range of critical vocal features, such as pitch and formant frequencies, essential for understanding the emotional variations in speech.",
    "Additionally, to delve deeper into the contextual information of speech, we utilized the SLSTM technique [15].",
    "SLSTM captures subtle variations and long-term dependencies in speech signals through time-series modeling, providing a more comprehensive approach to speech emotion recognition [16].For facial expression feature extraction, we used the FACET software [17].",
    "FACET is an advanced facial expression analysis tool that can identify and quantify various micro-expressions and emotional features on the face."
  ],
